BY BO Staff Writer “The ANC is very strange because the Communist Party initially was supposed to play this radicalising role but the Communist Party is the right wing of the ANC. So you have therefore no left agent that is pushing the ANC to the Black Agenda and to the left direction. So we need to think carefully down the line in the long term …” BLF President Andile Mngxitama, speaking recently to a group of ANC RET comrades, reflects on the gap left by the Communist Party in its incapacity to push the ANC to the left. Listen to the full message here: